SUMMARY:SF Daytime Social- SALSA & BACHATA Party!
DESCRIPTION:SF Daytime Social – Salsa & Bachata Sundays at Verdi Club!\n🗓 Every 1st Sunday | 🕒3PM–9PM\n📍 Verdi Club\, 2424 Mariposa St (Mission District\, SF)\n🎟 $15 Entry – includes 2 dance workshops!\n🚘 Plenty of parking: street & dedicated lot! \nEvery 1st Sunday of the month in San Francisco @ Verdi Club- BE PART OF THIS HISTORIC EVENT! \nSPECIAL PERFORMANCES:\nTBA \n2 DJs:\nDJ Thiencito (San Francisco)\nGuest DJ \nInstructors:\nAntonio & Natsu\nJavi & Special Guest\nBoth classes are INT/Open \nLooking for a fun\, friendly way to dance your 1st Sunday away? Come vibe with us at the SF Daytime Social – where the music is fire\, the community is warm\, and the energy is always on point! \nWhether you’re just getting started or have been dancing for years\, this is a space where everyone’s welcome and everyone dances. \n🕓 Schedule:\n3PM – Bachata Class (Intermediate/Open)\n4PM – Salsa Class (Intermediate/Open)\n5–9PM – Dance Party with rotating 3 Salsa / 2 Bachata tracks\, all night! \n🎧 Music by amazing local + international DJs \n🕺 Classes designed to warm you up and get you connected\nInclusive vibes – leaders and followers ask each other to dance \nAnd let’s talk about this venue for a second… \nThe Verdi Club is an iconic San Francisco ballroom that’s been bringing people together since 1935. Think red velvet curtains\, vintage chandeliers\, a gorgeous dance floor\, and a welcoming community vibe. You’ll fall in love with the space the moment you step inside. \nNew to dancing? No worries. \nComing solo? You’ll leave with new friends.\nWant to start the week with a full heart? This is it. \nCome early\, dance lots\, laugh more\, and be part of the movement. \nSee you on the dance floor\, fam! \nEvent hosted by MaoMambo & SF Daytime Social crew.
URL:https://golatindance.com/event/sf-daytime-social-salsa-bachata-party-3pm-bachata-4pm-salsa-class-dancing-5pm-9pm-2/2026-04-05/
LOCATION:Verdi Club\, 2424 Mariposa Street\, San Francisco\, CA\, 94110\, United States
CATEGORIES:San Francisco
END:VEVENT
